<h2>Who Do You Want To Make Decision For You when you can't?</h2>
<p>
  The person you select as your agent is extremely important. This
  person may make health care decisions on your behalf if you cannot
  and may have to decide when to stop treatments. It is important that
  you select someone who understands how you want to be treated and will
  fight for that if necessary. 
</p>
<p>
  Your agent will have authority to make all health care choices for you
  if the primary doctor treating you determines that you are not able to 
  make your own choices. You should talk about what you want with your 
  agent. Your conversation with them should go into at least as much depth
  as the wishes you capture here. Your agent may decline the responsibility
  as your agent, so make sure you pick someone who you know can make the
  right decisions under uncertain circumstances. 
</p>

<div class="dynamic_bordered_box form">
  <div class="title">
    Who would you like to make medical choices on your behalf if
    you cannot make them yourself?
  </div>
  <%= form_for(@agent) do |f| %>
    <% if @agent.errors.any? %>
      <div id="error_explanation">
        <h2><%= pluralize(@agent.errors.count, "error") %> prohibited this agent from being saved:</h2>

        <ul>
          <% @agent.errors.full_messages.each do |msg| %>
            <li><%= msg %></li>
          <% end %>
        </ul>
      </div>
    <% end %>

    <div class="single_input">
      <%= f.label :name, 'Agent\'s Name:' %>
      <%= f.text_field :name, :class => 'long' %>
    </div>
    <div class="single_row">
      <div class="single_input first">
        <%= f.label :home_phone, 'Home Phone:' %>
        <%= f.text_field :home_phone, :class => 'medium' %>
      </div>
      <div class="single_input">
        <%= f.label :cell_phone, "Cell Phone:" %>
        <%= f.text_field :cell_phone, :class => 'medium' %>
      </div>
      <div class="clear"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="single_input">
      <%= f.label :address, 'Address:' %>
      <%= f.text_field :address, :class => 'long' %>
    </div>
    <div class="single_row">
      <div class="single_input first">
        <%= f.label :city, "City:" %>
        <%= f.text_field :city, :class => 'medium' %>
      </div>
      <div class="single_input">
        <label>
          &nbsp;
        </label>
        <%= f.select :state, UsState::NAMES %>
      </div>
      <div class="single_input">
        <%= f.label :zip, 'Zip Code' %>
        <%= f.text_field :zip, :class => 'small' %>
      </div>
      <div class="clear"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="single_input">
      <%= f.label :relationship, 'Relationship:' %>
      <%= f.text_field :relationship, :class => 'long' %>
    </div>

  <% end %>
</div>


